"'''No Disintegrations, Please'''" is a short story written by [[Paul Danner]] that was originally published in [[Star Wars Adventure Journal 14|''Star Wars Adventure Journal'' 14]] by [[West End Games]] in [[August]] [[1997]]. It was later reprinted in the short-story anthology ''[[Tales from the New Republic]]'' published by [[Bantam Spectra]] in [[December]] [[1999]]. In it, [[Boba Fett/Legends|Boba Fett]] takes on an entire [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] garrison. The story is notable for its expansion of Fett's abilities, tactics, and character.

==Plot summary==
A storyteller spins a tale about [[Boba Fett/Legends|Boba Fett]] for [[Youngling/Legends|urchins]]. In the story, Fett is hired to track down a fugitive [[Slicer/Legends|slicer]] for [[Jabba Desilijic Tiure/Legends|Jabba the Hutt]]. His quarry, [[Rivo Xarran]], is being harbored by his brother, [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] [[General/Legends|General]] [[Gaege Xarran]] in a [[Garrison/Legends|garrison]] base. Fett decimates the Imperial forces. Fett allows Rivo to barter for his life but also promises to one day finish the job. As the storyteller finishes his tale, he is visited by Boba Fett. Jabba, and thus the [[Bounty/Legends|bounty]] placed on Rivo Xarran, is long [[Death/Legends|dead]]. Fett gives the storyteller, who is revealed to be Rivo, [[Galactic Credit Standard/Legends|credits]] equal to his bounty before departing.

==Continuity==
Beyond [[Jabba Desilijic Tiure/Legends|Jabba the Hutt]] already being [[Death/Legends|dead]], there is no specific indication as to when the story is being told. The [[The Essential Reader's Companion|''Companion'']] estimates it occurred around the time of [[Boba Fett/Legends|Fett's]] return to public activity in the [[Star Wars: Dark Empire|Dark Empire]] comics.<ref name="TERC" />

